Grease and line a 30 x 23cm deep tin with baking paper.Put the peanut butter, honey and vanilla extract in a large microwaveable bowl and microwave for 45 seconds. Stir well and heat for another 10 seconds, until melted and smooth. Stir in the remaining ingredients until everything is fully coated.Tip into the prepared tin and press down evenly with wet hands. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or until solid.Slice into 24 bars. Transfer to a sealed container and keep in the fridge for up to 1 week.